1578
01:32:53.028 --> 01:32:56.798
So the TED proteins are the transcriptional effectors of the Hippo pathway,

1579
01:32:57.468 --> 01:33:01.428
and they become activated following the binding of coactivator proteins called Yap

1580
01:33:01.448 --> 01:33:05.068
or Taz. And together, they regulate the expression of a number of

1581
01:33:05.108 --> 01:33:08.618
genes broadly important in cancer cell survival, and

1582
01:33:08.708 --> 01:33:11.298
importantly for the context of today, drug resistance.

1583
01:33:12.248 --> 01:33:15.528
So normally, upstream signaling feeds into the activity of LATs

1584
01:33:15.608 --> 01:33:19.528
kinases, which control the phosphorylation status of Yap and

1585
01:33:19.588 --> 01:33:22.698
Taz, and thereby its subcellular localization.

1586
01:33:23.528 --> 01:33:27.268
But in addition to this canonical pathway regulation, it's

1587
01:33:27.328 --> 01:33:30.488
also been appreciated that TED proteins can be

1588
01:33:30.528 --> 01:33:33.948
posttranslationally modified in such a way that affects their function.

1589
01:33:34.668 --> 01:33:38.208
And that's by a posttranslational modification called palmitoylation,

1590
01:33:38.968 --> 01:33:42.848
which occurs on all four of the TED proteins in a region called the

1591
01:33:42.888 --> 01:33:46.748
central pocket. And it's been shown that the palmitoylation event is

1592
01:33:46.788 --> 01:33:50.418
important to promote Yap/Taz binding and transcriptional

1593
01:33:50.548 --> 01:33:51.028
output.

1594
01:33:51.848 --> 01:33:55.378
So with this discovery, a number of companies have been developing small

1595
01:33:55.408 --> 01:33:59.228
molecules, which are called central pocket palmitoylation inhibitors or

1596
01:33:59.328 --> 01:33:59.948
CPIs,

1597
01:34:00.828 --> 01:34:03.998
which bind the central pocket, inhibit palmitoylation,

1598
01:34:04.568 --> 01:34:08.238
thereby affect Yap and Taz binding and transcriptional activity.

1599
01:34:09.328 --> 01:34:12.388
And an alternative modality to inhibit this

1600
01:34:12.408 --> 01:34:16.328
pathway involves the development of small molecule protein-protein

1601
01:34:16.388 --> 01:34:20.228
interaction inhibitors, which also bind to TED but in a region

1602
01:34:20.308 --> 01:34:24.268
outside of the central pocket and can also displace Yap/Taz binding

1603
01:34:24.308 --> 01:34:26.688
and turn off transcriptional activity.

1604
01:34:26.908 --> 01:34:30.568
So in the talk today, I'll be comparing the activity of the

1605
01:34:31.168 --> 01:34:34.868
compound AZD0751, which is a palmitoylation

1606
01:34:34.888 --> 01:34:36.068
inhibitor, a CPI,

1607
01:34:36.908 --> 01:34:40.848
to the Novartis clinical candidate, IAG 933, which

1608
01:34:40.888 --> 01:34:42.188
is a Yap/TED PPI.

1609
01:34:44.448 --> 01:34:48.058
So it's been shown broadly in the literature that TED pathway activation

1610
01:34:48.088 --> 01:34:51.788
occurs as an adaptive resistance mechanism to a number of targeted

1611
01:34:51.797 --> 01:34:55.228
therapies, including EGFR inhibitors and KRAS

1612
01:34:55.268 --> 01:34:55.888
inhibitors.

